00:19:50.030 --> 00:19:54.890 align:middle line:10%
of thing we're dealing with here
will be seen as solid and as

00:19:54.890 --> 00:19:58.370 align:middle line:10%
scientific in the 21st century.

00:19:58.370 --> 00:20:01.178 align:middle line:84%
I'll look back at some of the
fuzzy stuff that was going

00:20:01.178 --> 00:20:03.730 align:middle line:90%
on in the name of behaviorism.

00:20:03.730 --> 00:20:05.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:20:05.810 --> 00:20:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Many scientists,
neuroscientists, today it's

00:20:10.550 --> 00:20:13.610 align:middle line:84%
almost axiomatic when they
talk about the mind, which

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:14.630 align:middle line:90%
they sometimes do.

00:20:14.630 --> 00:20:17.450 align:middle line:84%
They say the mind is sort
of located in the brain.

00:20:17.450 --> 00:20:20.060 align:middle line:84%
I gather that that
way of putting it

00:20:20.060 --> 00:20:25.940 align:middle line:84%
is totally discordant with
your own view of things.

00:20:25.940 --> 00:20:27.332 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, I think--

00:20:27.332 --> 00:20:29.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are lots of
different ways of phrasing.

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:33.650 align:middle line:84%
This one is that
the mental phenomena

00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:37.580 align:middle line:84%
are emergent properties
of how the brain works.

00:20:37.580 --> 00:20:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And so it's almost
like brain is secreting

00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:43.630 align:middle line:90%
vision and mind and all that.

00:20:43.630 --> 00:20:45.830 align:middle line:84%
But maybe a better
way of talking

00:20:45.830 --> 00:20:50.540 align:middle line:84%
about it would be to say
that mental phenomena arise

00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:53.870 align:middle line:84%
through the interaction
between brain

00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:57.260 align:middle line:90%
and body and the environment.

00:20:57.260 --> 00:20:59.330 align:middle line:84%
And that whole
interactive, this is

00:20:59.330 --> 00:21:02.600 align:middle line:84%
sort of what Karl Popper says,
that whole interactive thing

00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:09.430 align:middle line:84%
produces an emergent, which we
call mind and spirit and so on.

00:21:09.430 --> 00:21:14.060 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's a better
way than just thinking

00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:16.356 align:middle line:90%
of the brain secreting it.

00:21:16.356 --> 00:21:20.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, how does this model
relate to human potential?

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:23.840 align:middle line:84%
If I want to cultivate my
various potentialities,

00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:26.150 align:middle line:84%
my skills, reach into
the implicate order

00:21:26.150 --> 00:21:29.510 align:middle line:84%
and make some of
it more explicate,

00:21:29.510 --> 00:21:32.600 align:middle line:84%
do you have notions
about that for learning,

00:21:32.600 --> 00:21:34.190 align:middle line:90%
for human development?

00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:36.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you said it
yourself just now.

00:21:36.290 --> 00:21:38.360 align:middle line:84%
You reach into the
implicate order.

00:21:38.360 --> 00:21:40.220 align:middle line:90%
You allow yourself.

00:21:40.220 --> 00:21:44.480 align:middle line:84%
Freud called it regression
in service of the ego

00:21:44.480 --> 00:21:46.730 align:middle line:84%
to primary process
kinds of things,

00:21:46.730 --> 00:21:49.870 align:middle line:84%
which are more holonomic,
more holographic like.

00:21:49.870 --> 00:21:52.910 align:middle line:90%


00:21:52.910 --> 00:21:58.490 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I think that's the general
way that I would say that.

00:21:58.490 --> 00:21:59.290 align:middle line:90%
This is different.

00:21:59.290 --> 00:22:01.190 align:middle line:90%
The other is imitation.

00:22:01.190 --> 00:22:04.580 align:middle line:84%
And the kind of thing
that we have role models.

00:22:04.580 --> 00:22:08.900 align:middle line:84%
And we take care of
ourselves in terms of model

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:12.880 align:middle line:84%
ourselves on
someone and the kind

00:22:12.880 --> 00:22:15.620 align:middle line:84%
of thing you do in sports
when you watch a videotape

00:22:15.620 --> 00:22:16.470 align:middle line:90%
or something.

00:22:16.470 --> 00:22:19.810 align:middle line:84%
>> And would you say
creativity works the same way?

00:22:19.810 --> 00:22:24.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, creativity works the
same way in the following sense

00:22:24.190 --> 00:22:28.780 align:middle line:84%
that we allow ourselves to get,
let's just be very crude here,

00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:33.490 align:middle line:84%
into this waveform, where
one distributed system.

00:22:33.490 --> 00:22:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And this, then, allows
the fluctuations

00:22:36.100 --> 00:22:40.630 align:middle line:84%
that take place there
to create new forms,

00:22:40.630 --> 00:22:44.200 align:middle line:84%
which, in space-time, we
can't really do too well.

00:22:44.200 --> 00:22:46.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, things are
already formed.

00:22:46.780 --> 00:22:51.610 align:middle line:84%
But if we get back into this
potential distributed implicate

00:22:51.610 --> 00:22:55.090 align:middle line:84%
type of order, then
these fluctuations

00:22:55.090 --> 00:22:58.630 align:middle line:84%
have a chance to
reorganize as a way,

00:22:58.630 --> 00:23:01.557 align:middle line:84%
or to organize new
foci of activity.

00:23:01.557 --> 00:23:03.640 align:middle line:84%
>> And these would take
the shape of mental images

00:23:03.640 --> 00:23:06.310 align:middle line:90%
in our mind?

00:23:06.310 --> 00:23:08.470 align:middle line:84%
>> By the time they get
to be mental images,

00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:12.730 align:middle line:84%
it's already pretty well
set into space-time form.

00:23:12.730 --> 00:23:15.520 align:middle line:84%
>> What is a mental
image in space-time?

00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:18.160 align:middle line:84%
How would you describe
that as a neuroscientist?

00:23:18.160 --> 00:23:21.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I've got my image
of your face right now.

00:23:21.800 --> 00:23:24.760 align:middle line:84%
And I also have an
image of Brook sitting

00:23:24.760 --> 00:23:28.000 align:middle line:84%
in a chair over
there and a big eye

00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:32.210 align:middle line:84%
looking at me in front, a
television eye, with my eyes

00:23:32.210 --> 00:23:33.010 align:middle line:90%
closed.

00:23:33.010 --> 00:23:35.140 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's mental imagery.

00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:38.100 align:middle line:84%
>> You wouldn't try and tie that
to resonant neural patterns?

00:23:38.100 --> 00:23:41.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, sure, I'll
be happy to do that.

00:23:41.620 --> 00:23:43.540 align:middle line:84%
There are two
kinds of mechanism.

00:23:43.540 --> 00:23:47.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can sort of divide
things up into twos and threes

00:23:47.260 --> 00:23:48.230 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:23:48.230 --> 00:23:50.080 align:middle line:84%
But if you divide
neural activity,

00:23:50.080 --> 00:23:54.850 align:middle line:84%
you can divide into propagated
nerve impulses on the one hand

00:23:54.850 --> 00:23:58.310 align:middle line:84%
and then these slow
potentials, hyperpolarizations,

00:23:58.310 --> 00:24:01.340 align:middle line:84%
de-polarizations that
don't go anywhere.

00:24:01.340 --> 00:24:05.920 align:middle line:84%
And they form this sort of
holographic like pattern.

00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:10.600 align:middle line:84%
And it's those that I feel,
and have some evidence

00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:16.080 align:middle line:84%
to support this, are what
we experience as images.

00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:19.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Would these sort of be like
standing waves in the minds?

00:24:19.940 --> 00:24:20.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Well--

00:24:20.740 --> 00:24:22.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Am I reaching too far here?

00:24:22.300 --> 00:24:23.880 align:middle line:84%
>> You said it in
the mind again.

00:24:23.880 --> 00:24:24.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:24:24.790 --> 00:24:26.438 align:middle line:90%
>> The waves aren't in the mind.

00:24:26.438 --> 00:24:27.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Standing waves in the brain.

00:24:27.730 --> 00:24:28.810 align:middle line:90%
>> In the brain.

00:24:28.810 --> 00:24:30.790 align:middle line:84%
They could be
thought of that way.

00:24:30.790 --> 00:24:34.780 align:middle line:84%
Or as, again, I use the
matrix analogy as well,

00:24:34.780 --> 00:24:37.390 align:middle line:84%
just so we don't get
too far into the waves.

00:24:37.390 --> 00:24:41.020 align:middle line:84%
But sure, some kind
of standing waveforms

00:24:41.020 --> 00:24:43.720 align:middle line:90%
that are there temporarily.

00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:45.220 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes it lasts longer.

00:24:45.220 --> 00:24:46.810 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes
they're very brief.

00:24:46.810 --> 00:24:49.100 align:middle line:84%
And we are not
even aware of them.

00:24:49.100 --> 00:24:53.590 align:middle line:84%
But the longer they last,
Sherrington had this idea.

00:24:53.590 --> 00:24:58.450 align:middle line:84%
And he said there seems to
be a reciprocal relationship

00:24:58.450 --> 00:25:00.830 align:middle line:90%
between reflex and mind.

00:25:00.830 --> 00:25:04.863 align:middle line:84%
The more reflex, the less
mental and vice versa.

00:25:04.863 --> 00:25:05.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, OK.

00:25:05.770 --> 00:25:08.620 align:middle line:84%
That relates somehow to
free will also, I gather.

00:25:08.620 --> 00:25:15.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there we get into a
different set of problems now.

00:25:15.580 --> 00:25:22.200 align:middle line:10%
Sure, to some extent, if you get
into your potential mode, then

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:24.580 align:middle line:10%
new fluctuation, new
things can happen.

00:25:24.580 --> 00:25:26.710 align:middle line:10%
But usually, free
will is conceived

00:25:26.710 --> 00:25:31.270 align:middle line:10%
of in terms of how many
constraints are operating.

00:25:31.270 --> 00:25:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And we have in statistics a
notion of degrees of freedom.

00:25:35.980 --> 00:25:36.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:25:36.780 --> 00:25:41.570 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think our
will, essentially,

00:25:41.570 --> 00:25:45.450 align:middle line:90%
is constrained more or less.

00:25:45.450 --> 00:25:47.920 align:middle line:84%
We have so many
degrees of freedom.

00:25:47.920 --> 00:25:53.276 align:middle line:84%
And the more degrees of freedom
we have, the more we feel free.

00:25:53.276 --> 00:25:56.720 align:middle line:90%
And we have freedom of choice.

00:25:56.720 --> 00:25:59.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, what can we say
in wrapping the program up,

00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:02.620 align:middle line:84%
given all of these aspects
of the mind-brain system that

00:26:02.620 --> 00:26:03.640 align:middle line:90%
you've described?

00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:07.270 align:middle line:84%
How does that relate to, say,
the ultimate or the farther

00:26:07.270 --> 00:26:10.570 align:middle line:90%
reaches of human potential?

00:26:10.570 --> 00:26:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think in
the 21st century,

00:26:12.470 --> 00:26:16.120 align:middle line:84%
we're going to be able to do an
awful lot that we weren't able

00:26:16.120 --> 00:26:22.600 align:middle line:84%
to do up to now, simply because
science will be admitted

00:26:22.600 --> 00:26:27.800 align:middle line:84%
to the spiritual aspects
of mankind and vice versa,

00:26:27.800 --> 00:26:31.510 align:middle line:84%
that what has been segregated
for at least 300 years since

00:26:31.510 --> 00:26:35.380 align:middle line:84%
Galileo were the
spiritual aspects,

00:26:35.380 --> 00:26:38.690 align:middle line:84%
in Western culture at least,
have been sort of relegated

00:26:38.690 --> 00:26:39.490 align:middle line:90%
over here.

00:26:39.490 --> 00:26:40.930 align:middle line:90%
And people have split this.

00:26:40.930 --> 00:26:42.740 align:middle line:90%
You know, we build buildings.

00:26:42.740 --> 00:26:44.260 align:middle line:90%
We do surgery.

00:26:44.260 --> 00:26:45.760 align:middle line:90%
And do all of these things.

00:26:45.760 --> 00:26:49.360 align:middle line:84%
And then we if have a
spiritual aspect to ourselves,

00:26:49.360 --> 00:26:50.780 align:middle line:90%
we go do that somewhere else.

00:26:50.780 --> 00:26:51.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Separate.

00:26:51.580 --> 00:26:54.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Whereas now, I think these
things will come together.

00:26:54.880 --> 00:26:57.850 align:middle line:84%
And it'll be perfectly all
right for what we today

00:26:57.850 --> 00:27:01.390 align:middle line:84%
call in quotes faith
healers to come and help

00:27:01.390 --> 00:27:06.610 align:middle line:84%
with reduction of pain and
to ease all kinds of things.

00:27:06.610 --> 00:27:09.560 align:middle line:84%
So you know, it'll
be a different world.

00:27:09.560 --> 00:27:15.870 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't even be surprised
if preventative therapies could

00:27:15.870 --> 00:27:20.940 align:middle line:84%
be instituted because they deal
with controls of ourselves.

00:27:20.940 --> 00:27:24.090 align:middle line:84%
So we aren't as
prone to get cancers.

00:27:24.090 --> 00:27:25.380 align:middle line:90%
>> That's very optimistic.

